<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Apple" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Apple,</orth> 1) the fruit of the apple-tree: <bibl n="shak. son 93.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 93, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.3.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 3, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.139" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 139</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.2.101" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.167" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 167</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.230.167" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 230</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.7.155" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 7, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.4.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 4, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.5.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 5, 16</bibl>.<lb />2) <emph>the a. of the eye</emph> == eye-ball: <cit><quote>sink in a. of his eye,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.104" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 104</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>and laugh upon the a. of her eye,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.475" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 475</bibl></cit> (i. e. perhaps: always laugh upon her, though she perhaps look another way?)
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>